article.description: Zach Lofton scored seven straight points, including a slam dunk for emphasis, and Texas Southern held on to post a 70-68 win over Alabama State Saturday night to maintain its hold on first-place
article.headline: Lofton powers Texas Southern past Alabama State, 70-68
article.linkText: Lofton powers Texas Southern past Alabama State, 70-68
article.story: HOUSTON -- Zach Lofton scored seven straight points, including a slam dunk for emphasis, and Texas Southern held on to post a 70-68 win over Alabama State Saturday night to maintain its hold on first-place in the Southwestern Conference. Alabama State tied the game with 1:40 left, 63-63 on a layup by Amir Warnock. Lofton answered with a three-point play with :29 left to give the Tigers the lead. Warnock converted a layup to make it a one-point game, 66-65, but missed a free throw that would have tied the game. Lofton hit a pair of free throws with :14 left and dunked with :04 left to make it 70-65 and the Hornets' Torloft Thomas hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer to set the final score. Lofton finished with 25 points for Texas Southern (11-10, 7-1). Rodney Simeon scored 17 points to lead Alabama State (5-15, 3-5).
